    "description": "The Telco customer churn dataset contains information about a fictional telco company that provided home phone and Internet services to 7043 customers in California in Q3. It indicates which customers have left, stayed, or signed up for their service. Multiple important demographics are included for each customer, as well as a Satisfaction Score, Churn Score, and Customer Lifetime Value (CLTV) index. It is designed to facilitate analysis of customer behavior and retention strategies."
  },
  "desc": "The Telco customer churn dataset contains information about a fictional telco company that provided home phone and Internet services to 7043 customers in California in Q3. It indicates which customers have left, stayed, or signed up for their service. Multiple important demographics are included for each customer, as well as a Satisfaction Score, Churn Score, and Customer Lifetime Value (CLTV) index. It is designed to facilitate analysis of customer behavior and retention strategies.",
  "goal": "Analyze the impact of different customer demographic factors (e.g., age, gender, income) on churn to identify which factors are most strongly associated with customer churn, helping the company understand the underlying reasons for churn.",
  "requirements": {
    "data": [
      {
        "id": "D1",
        "requirement": "The data should be separated into macro-level data (overview) and micro-level data (detail views). For the overview view, focus on the age distribution by gender for an initial overview. For the detail views, explore the relationship between customer lifetime value and satisfaction score, and identify churn status.",
        "reason": "This separation will help users understand general trends at the overview level while drilling down into specific details about customer segments."
      }
    ],
    "visualization": [
      {
        "id": "V1",
        "requirement": "Use a bar chart for the overview view to show the age distribution by gender. This will provide a clear visual representation of customer demographics.",
        "reason": "Bar charts are suitable for showing categorical data (gender) and numerical data (age) and can easily highlight trends."
      },
      {
        "id": "V2",
        "requirement": "Use a scatter plot for the exploration view to visualize the relationship between customer lifetime value and satisfaction scores, colored by churn status. This will help identify patterns related to churn.",
        "reason": "Scatter plots are ideal for visualizing the relationship between two quantitative variables and can effectively show how customer lifetime value and satisfaction scores vary with churn status."
      }
    ],
    "interaction": [
      {
        "id": "I1",
        "requirement": "Add a point selection interaction to both views to allow users to filter data based on specific gender and age groups. The selected data should highlight in the detail views.",
        "reason": "Point selection provides users with the ability to focus on specific segments of the data, making it easier to understand subtle patterns and trends."
      }
    ]
  },
